The dialogue is put, apparently, in the last year of Cato’s long life, and represents the old man ¹ discoursing, calmly and cheer- fully, with the younger Scipio (Aemilianus), brother—in-law of Cato’s elder son, and his friend LaeliuS, the same who gives his name to the dialogue on friendship.
